Monkey 5514 lived a very happy and productive life, and had familial relationships with many of his tribe and friendships with nearly everyone he met. He never seemed to do someone the wrong way, nor come across any grievances he didn't seek to correct. As he got older, Monkey 5514 predictably had more health complications, such as arthritis and some heart problems. One bright, sunny day, as he sat thinking about his blessings at the ripe age of 50, he felt pains in his chest and died later that day of cardiac arrest. He wasn't in agony, but died a quiet, simple death for a quiet, simple life.
